author: Kpaxs
text: If you want to be excellent: Stop trying to be unique. Stop asking "what's my angle?" Stop looking for your niche before you've developed your competence. Instead, focus on the fundamentals. Study the masters. Do the work. Build the skills. Develop your taste. Pursue quality

text:
The magic you’re looking for is in the full-assed effort you’re avoiding.

It’s amazing how many people will rationalize avoiding skill development on the grounds of “nah bro, I’d rather have a life.”

The thing is, you can make serious progress climbing pretty much any skill
